div.p:
The hierarchic structure of a dictionary entry is enforced by the
structures defined in this module. The content model for
entry specifies that entries do not nest, that homographs
nest within entries, and that senses nest within entries, homographs,
or senses, and may be nested to any depth to reflect the embedding of
sub-senses. Any of the top-level constituents (def,
usg, form, etc.) can appear at any level (i.e.,
within entries, homographs, or senses).





&superEntry;















&entry;











&entryFree;











&hom;











&sense;











&dictScrap;
